(44, 13, 47, 28, 1, 10, 10, 'salvation unto the ends of the earth', 'Connection of Salvation and Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation extending beyond Israel. Acts highlights the Gentiles receiving salvation, while Hosea speaks of those once rejected becoming ''sons of the living God.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 47, 33, 4, 2, 3, 'light of the Gentiles', 'Connection of Salvation and Nations', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of nations in God''s plan for salvation. Acts 13:47 speaks of being a light to the Gentiles, while Micah 4:2 mentions many nations coming to the Lord.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
